<p class="article-lead">A perfume quality control checklist should connect each risk to an observable result and an approved reference.</p><h2>Liquid and filling</h2><p>Check fragrance/formula identity, appearance, material lots, fill quantity and batch coding. Record deviations.</p><h2>Closure and function</h2><p>Inspect crimp or torque, spray, priming, leakage, cap retention and visible assembly gaps using representative units.</p><h2>Decoration and packing</h2><p>Compare color, print position, labels, scent-artwork matching, carton assembly and case quantities with approved samples and artwork.</p><p>Define critical, major and cosmetic defects, sampling method and release authority before production. Keep retained samples and records for complaint investigation and repeat-order comparison.</p>
